  [ctns_front style='']
Y-Intercept<br/>Linear Function
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
The $$y$$-intercept of a function is the value of $$y$$ when $$x=0$$.
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
The y-intercept -- linear function.
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
The y-intercept of a function is the value of y when x equals 0.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
